# The server needs no env vars in dev — these are the only knobs it reads.
# (No dotenv: Render injects prod env, and dev runs fine on the defaults.)

# Port to listen on. Render injects its own; dev defaults to 3001.
#PORT=3001

# Comma-separated CORS allowlist override. When unset, production allows
# chaverola.com + www + Vercel preview deployments, and everything else
# allows localhost:5173 and 5174 (Vite's default port and its first
# fallback when 5173 is taken). See src/config.ts.
#CLIENT_ORIGINS=https://example.com,https://staging.example.com

# Gmail SMTP for the transcript email (feature 11). Both must be set or the
# mailer falls back to log-only mode — so dev leaves them unset and still
# needs zero env vars. In production, set both in Render's Environment tab.
# GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD is a 16-char Google app password with the spaces
# stripped, NOT your normal Gmail password. Setup steps: docs/operations.md
# → "Gmail app password". (There is no dotenv loader; Render injects these.)
#GMAIL_USER=you@gmail.com
#GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=abcdefghijklmnop
